5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to the utility gross receipts tax and utility
10 service use tax; to amend Sections 40-21-83 and 40-21-103,
11 Code of Alabama 1975, to exclude the use of natural gas or
12 electricity in commercial aquaculture aeration systems,
13 commercial greenhouses, pivot irrigation systems, and poultry
14 houses from the taxes.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Sections 40-21-83 and 40-21-103 of the Code
17 of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
18 "§40-21-83
19 There are specifically excluded from the gross receipts
20 or gross sales of a utility, all revenues derived from any of
21 the following:
22 (1) The furnishing of utility services which the State
23 of Alabama is prohibited from taxing under the Constitution or
24 laws of the United States of America or the Constitution of
25 the State of Alabama of 2022.
26 (2) The furnishing of utility services which are
27 otherwise taxed under Sections 40-23-1 to 40-23-36, inclusive.
28 (3) Wholesale sales.
Page 1

(3) Wholesale sales.
SB159 Engrossed
29 (4) The furnishing of electricity, natural gas, or
30 domestic water for use or consumption by, in, or for the
31 direct production, generation, processing, storage, delivery,
32 or transmission of electricity, natural gas, or domestic
33 water.
34 (5) The furnishing of electricity to a manufacturer or
35 compounder for use in an electrolytic or electrothermal
36 manufacturing or compounding process.
37 (6) The furnishing of natural gas to a manufacturer or
38 compounder as a chemical raw material in the manufacturing or
39 compounding of tangible personal property, but not as fuel or
40 energy.
41 (7) The furnishing of natural gas to be used by a
42 manufacturer or compounder to chemically convert raw materials
43 prior to the use of the converted raw materials in an
44 electrolytic or electrothermal manufacturing or compounding
45 process.
46 (8) The use or consumption of electricity by an
47 incorporated municipality, a board, or corporation organized
48 under the authority of any incorporated municipality in
49 furnishing or providing street lighting or traffic-control
50 systems; the use or consumption of telephone services by an
51 incorporated municipality in providing fire alarm systems; and
52 the use or consumption of domestic water by an incorporated
53 municipality in extinguishing fires, explosions, or
54 conflagrations.
55 (9)a. The furnishing of natural gas or electricity for
56 use or consumption as fuel or energy in and for the heating of
Page 2

use or consumption as fuel or energy in and for the heating of
SB159 Engrossed
57 commercial aquaculture aeration systems, commercial
58 greenhouses, pivot irrigation systems, and poultry houses.
59 b. The exclusion provided in this subdivision shall not
60 include the furnishing of natural gas or electricity for use
61 or consumption as fuel or energy in the production of
62 industrial hemp or hemp, as defined in Section 2-8-381, or
63 cannabis, as defined in Section 20-2A-3.
64 (10) The furnishing of utility services through the use
65 of a prepaid telephone calling card."
66 "§40-21-103
67 The storage, use, or other consumption of utility
68 services in the State of Alabama is hereby specifically
69 excluded from the tax herein levied:
70 (1) Whenever the State of Alabama is prohibited from
71 taxing such storage, use, or consumption under the
72 Constitution or laws of the United States of America or the
73 Constitution of the State of Alabama of 2022;
74 (2) Whenever any tax relating to the sale, use,
75 storage, or consumption of said utility services shall be
76 levied under the provisions of Article 2 of Chapter 23 of this
77 title, or under the provisions of Sections 40-23-1 through
78 40-23-36 or the Alabama Transaction Tax Act of 1992 if enacted
79 into law;
80 (3) Whenever the purchase of said utility services
81 shall have been at a wholesale sale;
82 (4) Whenever electricity, natural gas, or domestic
83 water shall have been used or consumed directly in or for the
84 production, generation, processing, storage, delivery, or
